The paper deals with the impact of authentication on the effective capacity of an underwater acoustic channel, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI) aspects. The paper also discusses the impersonation attack by a malicious node, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (CR). The use of artificial neural network (ANN) method for computing the optimal transmission rate indicates the involvement of machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Finally, the consideration of physical layer authentication and channel knowledge suggests the involvement of multimedia (MM) communication systems.
